headline: Martin Marietta Materials (NYSE:MLM) Misses Q4 CY2025 Revenue Estimates, Stock Drops
summary: Construction materials supplier Martin Marietta Materials (NYSE:MLM) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales falling 6% year on year to $1.53 billion. The company’s full-year revenue guidance of $6.6 billion at the midpoint came in 11% below analysts’ estimates. Its GAAP profit of $4.62 per share was 7.2% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
